{
  "answer": "**Manu’s *Manusmṛti* Chapter 7 grounds the king’s *daṇḍa* (rod of punishment) authority in both cosmology and pragmatics.** The king is divinely constituted from particles of gods like Indra, Agni, Yama, etc., making him a “great deity in human form,” whose fire “burns the whole family, with its cattle and store of wealth.”[^1] The Lord created *Daṇḍa* as “Dharma, the protector of all beings,” to which all submit out of fear.[^2] Pragmatically, without *Daṇḍa*, “the stronger would roast the weaker like fish on a spit”; “the crow would eat the sacrificial cake”; and “the lower [would] usurp the place of the higher,” corrupting all *varṇas*.[^3]\n\n**Viṣṇu’s *Viṣṇu Smṛti* Chapter 3 (the parallel *rājadharma* chapter) similarly grounds *daṇḍa* pragmatically as essential for order.** The king must “put to death those who harm [the state’s] constituent elements”; “put to death the wicked”; and wield the “dark, red-eyed rod of justice (*daṇḍa*) [that] moves without fear,” ensuring subjects prosper under just judgment.[^4] Less cosmologically elaborate here, it stresses protection of *varṇas*, *āśramas*, and property.\n\n**Manu’s framing is more violent**, with visceral, chaotic imagery of roasting humans, burning families, and predatory disorder—far beyond Viṣṇu’s drier commands to execute threats. In both, violence anchors **pragmatically** (averting anarchy, upholding hierarchy), though Manu layers **cosmology** atop it (divine origins of king/*Daṇḍa*).\n\n[^1]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 7, [p-9af453](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-9af453).\n[^2]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 7, [p-73f910](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-73f910), [p-55e886](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-55e886).\n[^3]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 7, [p-d56424](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-d56424) to [p-32b6e6](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-32b6e6).\n[^4]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, Chapter 3, [p-0a75df](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/03/translation/#p-0a75df), [p-df2345](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/03/translation/#p-df2345), [p-636919](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/03/translation/#p-636919).",
